Johannesburg – South African football giant, Kaizer Chiefs, announced that their upcoming match, which is meant to be played tomorrow, against PWD Bamenda hangs in the air. This comes after the Cameroonian side have requested through CAF a postponement of the CAF Champions League 2nd Leg Prelim match. Chiefs made the announcement via their Twitter account.   Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here. Sunday World Ashley Lechman